1.title: Snake Bitten
1.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Moonshine season is back and demand for white lightnin' is higher than ever. Tim's outlaw past catches up with him. Mark and Digger receive a sign from above.

2.title: Shine in the Sky
2.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Josh mashes in for the first time this season while awaiting word on Cutie Pie's fate. Mark and Digger build an experimental three-pot still.

3.title: Lightning Strikes
3.plot: With insider facts and exclusive Mega Moments - Josh needs a partner before his first run of the season. Patti and David hunt for clean water in Louisiana's swamplands.

4.title: Pony Express
4.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Mark and Digger are ready to test their three-pot still. Chico and Sondra employ a four-legged still hand. Josh rides under the radar in South Carolina.

5.title: Second Chances
5.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - After a disastrous first run on their three-pot still, Mark and Digger try to redeem themselves. Tim enlists Tickle as JT's moonshine mentor.

6.title: Legends of the Shine
6.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Tim and JT visit moonshine legends. Chico and Sondra run a batch of strawberry banana brandy. Mark and Digger test yeast strains to get the most out of a new 'shine recipe.

7.title: Pass the Juice
7.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Patti and David deal with a deadly intruder at their still site in Louisiana. Mark and Digger try something new to fix a stalled fermentation.

8.title: Stash and Grab
8.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Josh runs an old family recipe for his biggest sale of the season. Lance enlists the help of a bootlegger to move his product. Sondra thinks fast when a sale goes awry.

9.title: Arrested Development
9.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - In Virginia, Tickle mentors J.T. while Mark and Digger receive an impossible 'shine order. In Louisiana, Patti and David secure their still site after spotting a deadly intruder.

10.title: Skins in the Game
10.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Tim employs a centuries-old method for finding water at his new site. In Tennessee, Mark and Digger source ingredients for a unique liquor that could make their season.

11.title: Blowing Your Cover
11.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - In the Great Smoky Mountains, Mark and Digger prepare for their first run of hillbilly grappa. In Louisiana, Patti and David bootleg on the bayou.

12.title: Highway to Hell
12.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - On the cusp of his biggest moonshine deal yet, Josh embarks on a harrowing cross-country delivery. Then, America's first "Shiner in Chief" inspires a top-dollar batch of malted rye whiskey.

13.title: From the Flames
13.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Josh must make good with a biker gang after a trailer fire leaves him empty-handed. Tickle's first run of legal rye whiskey tempts him to return to the illegal side.

14.title: High and Dry
14.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Josh becomes a mad moonshine scientist. Mark and Digger scramble to complete a challenging run. Patti and David deliver their biggest sale yet on the Gulf of Mexico.

15.title: Lighted Up
15.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Mark and Digger confront a 'shiner who's been edging into their territory. Josh makes a split-second decision when red and blue lights flash.

16.title: Not a Crook
16.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Tim considers a permanent role for Tickle at the distillery. Sondra convinces Chico that a unique recipe will seal their season. Lance surprises Jeff with an unorthodox moonshine ingredient.

17.title: Foraging for a Long Winter Ahead
17.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Mike sets himself up for a career-high run of specialty liquor but faces a devastating setback. Sondra takes the reins for the final run of the season.

1.title: American Spirits
1.plot: With added facts and bonus scenes - Shine is in demand and the law is on the hunt. Jeff, Mark and Lance aim to double their profits while the law threatens to end Josh and Bill's season early.

2.title: Whiskey Burn
2.plot: With added facts, extra scenes and a glimpse of Tim's Moonshine Off-Time - Josh and Bill try to get a head start on their season; Patti and David hope to run their first batch of swamp shine.

3.title: Gone A-Rye
3.plot: With extra scenes, insider facts and a Mega Moment flashback - Tim breaks the news about the fate of Climax Moonshine. Jeff, Mark and Lance search for a new site before rivals can grab hold of the market.

4.title: Still Life
4.plot: With added facts, extra scenes and a glimpse of Mark Ramsey's Moonshine Off-Time Bill and Josh still have no shine. Mark and Digger seek out a legend to fix their noxious blend.

5.title: Rain or Shine
5.plot: With added facts, extra scenes and a glimpse of Josh's Moonshine Off-Time - Josh and Bill struggle to finally make their first run. Mark and Digger's rye test leaves them exposed. Tim's reeling after a deadly disaster.

6.title: Scotch on the Rocks
6.plot: With added facts, extra scenes and a glimpse of Digger's Moonshine Off-Time - Jeff, Mark and Lance are seeing red when they have to remake a batch of highland scotch.

7.title: Six Feet Undercover
7.plot: With added facts, extra scenes and a glimpse of David's Moonshine Off-Time - Mark and Digger have a stockpile of apple-rye brandy to sell. Now the team just needs to turn their wealth of 'shine into hard-earned cash.

8.title: Out on a Limb
8.plot: With added facts, extra scenes and a glimpse of David's Moonshine Off-Time - A North Carolina behemoth threatens Josh and Bill's bunker.

9.title: Trouble Brewing
9.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - As summer winds down, the 'shiners feel the pressure to make a quick dollar. Tim's traversed an ocean to expand his territory, but his sales pitch is lost in translation.

10.title: Caved In
10.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Josh fears the fight with Bill has left their partnership beyond repair. Patti and David need to double down on a scorching new brew, but they end up running for their lives.

11.title: Cherry Bounce
11.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Tim bets the farm to fill a massive international order; it's judgment day in court for Tickle, and Mark and Digger could be up a creek without a mash barrel.

12.title: Shine 'Til You Drop
12.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Moonshine season is coming to a close and Mark and Digger are left looking for a new still site. Patti and David's jalapeno whiskey puts them on unfamiliar ground.

13.title: Still Regretting
13.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Jim Tom lends Josh a helping hand. Meanwhile, Tim can't catch a break and production grinds to a halt.

14.title: Virgin Whiskey
14.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Jim Tom and Josh make a run at Josh's deep woods still site, while Chico and Sandra 'shine creekside. Mark and Jeff wheel and deal to make their 100K season goal.

15.title: Presidential Shine
15.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - A new pen pal may bring Mark and Digger's season to an end. Jeff, Mark and Lance channel a founding father to save their season.

16.title: End of an Era
16.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - All good 'shine must come to an end. Tim's order from Europe may shut down Belmont Farm Distillery. Mark and Digger get a shock in the middle of a sale.

1.title: Whiskey Rebellion
1.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - It's springtime in Appalachia. Josh sets out to reap the benefits of 'shining solo all winter, but Cutie Pie goes missing and he makes a costly mistake.

2.title: Take Me to the River
2.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - A 'shiner gets arrested, opening up a new territory for Mark and Jeff. Patti and David begin their season with a batch of mayhaw brandy.

3.title: Hard Start
3.plot: With added facts, extra scenes and a Mega Moment flashback - A permanent injury has Josh in need of a helping hand. Chico and Sandra disguise their new still site as a hunter's blind.

4.title: Luck of the Irish
4.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Big Chuck's rookie mistake draws unwanted visitors to Josh's still site. Tim shows Irish whiskey distillers a thing or two about American moonshine.

5.title: Big River Redemption
5.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Mark calls on Jim Tom when he needs a partner for his new Tennessee operation. Big Chuck goes back in time to find a new still site for Josh.

6.title: Whiskey Time Machine
6.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Tim enlists the help of inventors to turn his moonshine into whiskey. To double their output, Mark and Digger add a dangerous steamer still to their operation.

7.title: Dog Days of Shining
7.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Josh salvages a piece of Moonshiners history for his new still site. Mark and Mike have a brush with the law after making their first run of Tennessee 'shine.

8.title: Smokey Mountain Gin
8.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Tim risks $10,000 worth of moonshine to test his new whiskey time machine. Mark and Digger get creative when they receive an order for high-dollar mountain gin.

9.title: Green Dragon
9.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Mark and Digger make "moon gin" for a high-rolling customer. Jeff gets bent on Lance's absinthe while Mark begins to question their age-old partnership.

10.title: Big City Bootleg
10.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Josh and Big Chuck go underground to build their new stash house. Mark and Digger travel to Nashville to make the biggest sale of their careers.

11.title: Big Wheels Keep on Turning
11.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Josh and Big Chuck rebuild an old trough to feed their water wheel. Mark and Digger enlist the help of a moonshining legend.

12.title: The Green Devil
12.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Patti and David follow the harvest with a pear-in-the-bottle brandy. Jeff and Lance make another run of their mountain absinthe, but is it too expensive for their market?

13.title: Thunder Pumpkins
13.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Mark and Digger make a batch of hazelnut rum with the help of legendary moonshiner JB. Tim hawks his rapid-aged whiskey at a trade show.

14.title: Two Pot Bang Bang
14.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Mark and Digger make rye apple moonshine with their copper two-pot still. Mark and Mike bootleg their corn liquor by boat to avoid the law.

15.title: Intruder Alert
15.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - Josh and Big Chuck are confronted with an intruder who leaves them deep in a hole. Mark and Digger have a close call with the law.

16.title: Last Call
16.plot: With added facts and extra scenes - In this season finale, Tim and Tickle reunite when Tickle gets released from jail. Mark and Jeff's legendary partnership comes to a bittersweet end.
